rp-text&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;I was running a broad crawl (20+ thousand seeds) using the late=
st SNAPSHOT build of Heritrix (3.1.2-20130625) when I noticed that one of o=
ur big blogging site wasn&#39;t making much progress.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
As it turned out=
 it was making intermittent progress and then hitting large stretches of ti=
me where every fetch attempt ended with a -2 (connect fail).&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
My in=
itial thought was that we were being blocked by the website, but that did n=
ot turn out to be the case. Additional inspection of the crawl log revealed=
 that during a 20+ million URL crawl over 14 thousand URLs had errored out =
with a -2. I compared this with our most recent comparable crawl and for th=
at the number was 60 URLs out of 40+ million. Clearly there was a problem w=
ith the crawler.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
While some domains were affect and other not, I c=
ould not deduce any pattern as to what domains or URLs this affected.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;=
br&gt;
My second assumption then was that this was due to me running a SNAPSHO=
T build. So I put 3.1.0-RC1 (which I had used for the previous crawl) into =
play on the same machine. The issue reoccurred. -2 errors began showing up =
in the crawl log about 2 hours in (exactly when the 500 second wait times b=
etween 15 retries period had passed). This is not a regression in Heritrix.=
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
That left two variables. The fact that I was running on new hardw=
are and that I had upgraded from Java 6 to 7 (1.7.0_25-b15 to be exact).&lt;br=
&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
I then installed Java 1.6.0-b105 and tried the crawl a third time (a=
gain using the SNAPSHOT build), shortening the retry wait interval from 500=
 seconds to 50. I figured this could only make the issue worse and would me=
an that it could manifest in as little as 15 minutes, instead of 2 hours.&lt;b=
r&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Now 5.5 hours in there are no sign of URLs with inexplicable -2 sta=
tus codes. It seems the issue IS related to the Java version.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Has =
anyone encountered this? Any ideas on cause or how this could be remedied? =
For now, just using an older version of Java will fix the issue, but that i=
sn&#39;t a long term solution.&lt;br&gt;
